  "response_text": "A small animated character, the Noid, sits astride a bronze, rocket-shaped control device in a dark arcade-like setting filled with blurred colored lights. He has a red, tight-fitting suit with long floppy rabbit-like ears, white gloves, red shoes, a round “N” emblem on his chest, and a helmet with goggles and earphone-like attachments. The rocket nose points left and has a glowing tip; on its side are the words “LOW” and “HIGH” beside a lightning-bolt graphic. The Noid grips a control and gestures broadly, looking gleeful and mischievous.\n\nA large arcade cabinet comes into view with a bright sign reading “PIZZA Delivery GAME,” surrounded by yellow starburst pizza-slice symbols. Below the sign, a digital-looking label reads “ORDINARY DELIVERED PIZZA.” On the game screen, small yellow, boxy pizza icons drift across a gray background. From the right side, the Noid sits at the controls, aiming a bright green beam or zapper at the moving targets. When the beam strikes, a target flashes into a glowing green square or scribbled burst, as if being destroyed or disabled. The glossy arcade control panel reflects the green flashes and the cabinet graphics.\n\nThe Noid is then shown closer, still in his red suit and goggles, clutching his round handheld control. His mouth is wide open in a grin, fists raised with confidence. As he looks ahead, his expression shifts: his eyes widen behind the goggles, his smile fades, and he turns sideways with a worried, suspicious look.\n\nThe arcade display changes. A new header reads “BEST DELIVERED PIZZA,” with the word “BEST” inside a yellow starburst. On the screen below, a Domino’s delivery worker appears, wearing a blue cap and a red-and-blue uniform shirt with a name patch. Small white text along the bottom reads “Limited delivery area.” The image then changes to an open white pizza box holding a full Domino’s pizza topped with melted cheese, pepperoni, olives, mushrooms, green peppers, and sausage. The front edge of the box reads “Domino’s Pizza Delivers.”\n\nSuddenly, many small Domino’s Pizza box logos begin multiplying across the pizza image, layering over it until the screen is covered in a neat repeating pattern of red-and-blue Domino’s Pizza boxes. The header above still reads “BEST DELIVERED PIZZA.” A green beam descends toward the display, but the grid of Domino’s boxes remains in place.\n\nBack on the rocket device, the Noid leans forward aggressively, one fist pulled back as if preparing another attack. His foot presses near the “LOW” and “HIGH” markings on the side of the rocket. The scene returns to the repeating field of Domino’s Pizza boxes. A vivid green blast erupts in the center, spreading outward in jagged rays, then sweeps diagonally across the boxes. The beam is broad and bright, but after it passes, the Domino’s box pattern is still visible and orderly.\n\nThe Noid reappears facing forward, now without the confident grin. His eyes are wide and his mouth hangs open in alarm. A green electrical glow crackles over him, outlining his body, ears, arms, and gloves like a shock passing through him. He flails with both hands spread, his long ears thrown outward and upward, then the green glow fades. He is left looking rattled and defeated, his ears drooping unevenly and his face slack with confusion. His expression settles into a weary, annoyed stare.\n\nThe commercial ends on a close-up of a hot, fully topped pizza filling the screen. Melted cheese stretches between pieces of pepperoni, black olive rings, mushrooms, green peppers, and crumbled sausage. At the lower left is the Domino’s Pizza logo, and across the bottom in large white script is the slogan “Nobody Delivers Better,” underlined with a sweeping stroke.",
